LaTeX provides a built-in mechanism to generate a table of contents (TOC) automatically. Here's an example of how to do it:

### Step 1: Include the `tocloft` package

To generate a table of contents, you need to include the `tocloft` package in your LaTeX document. Add the following line to your preamble:

```latex
\usepackage{tocloft}
```

### Step 2: Set up the TOC

To generate the TOC, you need to use the `\tableofcontents` command. This command should be placed after the `\begin{document}` command, but before the first section or chapter.

```latex
\documentclass{book}
\usepackage{tocloft}

\begin{document}

\tableofcontents

\chapter{Chapter 1}
\section{Section 1.1}
\section{Section 1.2}

\chapter{Chapter 2}
\section{Section 2.1}
\section{Section 2.2}

\end{document}
```

